added.title: Booby Trap House
added.description: After being left alone at home, Cyborg and Starfire booby trap the tower for safety.

added.title: The Streak Part 1
added.description: It's Crime Season and Robin is determined to continue his streak of stopping 52 crimes every year.

added.title: The Streak Part 2
added.description: Robin's streak of stopping 52 crimes every year is in jeopardy when members of his team are poached by Kid Flash.

added.title: Permanent Record
added.description: It's back to school as the Titans teach each other about science and grammar.

added.title: The Gold Standard
added.description: It's St. Patrick's Day and after wishing to become a leprechaun, Beast Boy becomes obsessed with gold.

added.title: Employee of the Month Redux
added.description: While the other Titans are trying to stop a cow-stealing UFO, Beast Boy gets a job to buy a moped.

added.title: Grube's Fairytales
added.description: Robin tries to teach the Titans valuable life lessons by reading them fairytales, but the others co-opt his stories and spin them into their own twisted yarns.

added.title: Squash & Stretch
added.description: The Titans learn about cartoon-style violence in order to get revenge on a snack-stealing squirrel.

added.title: Secret Garden
added.description: When Cyborg starts to rage out, Starfire takes him to her secret garden in the backyard to relax.

added.title: Beast Boy's St. Patrick's Day Luck, and It's Bad
added.description: The Titans (except Beast Boy) are cursed on St. Patrick's Day and must travel to the end of the rainbow for the cure.

added.title: Salty Codgers
added.description: Raven is delighted when the other Titans are magically turned into old people during a battle.

added.title: You're Fired
added.description: Beast Boy gets fired from the team and the Wonder Twins take his place.

added.title: The Fuss
added.description: Nicole tries, and fails, to hide her disappointment when Richard and the kids fail to remember her special day. Richard has to figure out what special day he has actually forgotten and then make it a day to remember or else!

added.title: The Vase
added.description: Sick of Granny Jojo's ugly gifts, Nicole encourages the kids to take matters into their own hands and accidentally break her latest hideous vase. But when Gumball, Darwin and Anais try to destroy it, they discover it is more robust than it seems.

added.title: The Blame
added.description: Gumball gives Billy his first taste of videogames but the sheer excitement causes him to pass out. His mother Felicity summons the PTA and threatens to ban video games all across Elmore. Gumball and Darwin are given three chances to prove that videogames can be a force for good. But when they fail, they decide to prove books can be just as dangerous.

added.title: The Stories
added.description: Fed up with having to listen to Molly's long, tedious anecdotes, Gumball and Darwin try to teach her how to make them sound more exciting. When this doesn't work, they decide their only option is to give Molly a story worth telling.

added.title: The Disaster
added.description: When Rob purchases a universal remote from the Awesome Store, he discovers can control the entire universe. He rewinds into the past and remembers Gumball had left him in The Void, leaving him scarred and in his current mutated shape. He uses the universal remote to destroy Gumball's life, whilst Gumball has to figure out what's going on before he's ejected once and for all.

added.title: The Butterfly
added.description: Gumball learns the true meaning of the butterfly effect. In Biology class, Gumball and Darwin are waiting for a butterfly to emerge from its chrysalis. Miss Simian warns them about the Butterfly Effect whereby the flap of an insect's wings can start a tornado on the other side of the world. Paying no heed, Gumball releases the emergent butterfly into the wild, where it causes havoc upon Elmore.

added.title: The Saint
added.description: Gumball doesn't believe anyone could really be as nice as Alan and sets out to find his breaking point. Alan is so good-natured that Gumball feels compelled to make him lose his temper. Despite turning the whole school against him, destroying his relationship with Carmen and even selling his parents, Alan remains understanding and happy. Defeated, Gumball and Darwin decide to adopt Alan's positive attitude to see if they can be more like Alan.Gumball and Darwin help Anais make up an imaginary friend who turns out to be all too real. Anais throws a party but no-one shows up as she has no friends or social skills. Gumball and Darwin help Anais make up an imaginary friend who, much to all their surprise, appears in front of them. Gumball and Darwin teach Anais and her new friend how to become friends but realize he might not be so imaginary after all.

added.title: The Downer
added.description: Gumball is in a funk that is proving hard to shake. Gumball refuses to get out of bed because he is in a lousy mood. When his family try to cheer him up Gumball wishes they'd all just disappear and, inexplicably, they do. At first he enjoys the solitude and doing just as he pleases but soon his mood threatens to take control of him completely.

added.title: The Tape
added.description: Gumball and Darwin fail to make some instant homemade movie classics.

added.title: The Internet
added.description: Gumball accidentally uploads a video of himself, and then demands The Internet take it down...personally!

added.title: The Finale
added.description: The Wattersons are surprised to discover that their past actions have consequences.

added.title: The DVD
added.description: Gumball is desperate to avoid a late fee on the rented dvd he accidentally destroyed.

added.title: The End
added.description: Gumball and Darwin are convinced that the world will end in 24 hours.

added.title: The Meddler
added.description: Gumball is embarrassed when Mom comes to school to spend some "quality time".

added.title: Primal
added.description: Have the Bears lost their survival instincts by living in the modern world? Grizz wants to know so he purposefully gets the Bears lost in the deep forest.

added.title: Nom Nom
added.description: When Nom Nom shows up on the Bears' doorstep, disheveled and deposed from his spot as cutest internet star ever after a recent meltdown, he enlists the Bears to help him regain his title.

added.title: Shush Ninjas
added.description: The Bears are fed up with the decay of etiquette at today's theaters. The Bears take it upon themselves to be the police of the theater, sneaking up like ninjas to shush people who ruin the movie for others with their bad manners.

added.title: Panda's Sneeze
added.description: Panda bears have a very adorable (and violent!) sneeze, and our Panda is no exception. When a Vine video of his very cute sneeze goes viral, Panda becomes a cute sensation, which causes Nom Nom to try to fend off of this new challenger to his throne.

added.title: The Kindergarten Kid
added.description: Steven and the Gems deal with a monster problem.

added.title: Buddy's Book
added.description: Steven and Connie take a trip to the library and discover a long forgotten book.

added.title: Mindful Education
added.description: Steven and Connie need to learn greater focus to take their training to the next level.

added.title: Storm in the Room
added.description: Steven goes into his room in the temple to look for answers.

added.title: Doug Out
added.description: Steven and Connie join Connie's father on a stake out.

added.title: Steven Floats
added.description: Steven is so excited to be back home that he jumps for joy and jumps way too high.

added.title: Drop Beat Dad
added.description: Steven helps Sour Cream put on a show, even though Sour Cream's stepdad doesn't approve of DJs.

added.title: Bubbled
added.description: Steven gets marooned in his bubble.

added.title: Shirt Club
added.description: Steven and Buck Dewey make t-shirts together.

added.title: Reformed
added.description: Steven, Amethyst and Garnet chase after a monster that's been loose in the Temple.

added.title: Cry for Help
added.description: Steven's favorite TV show gets interrupted by a magical disturbance.

added.title: When It Rains
added.description: Steven helps a friend who's afraid of thunderstorms.

added.title: Gem Glow
added.description: Steven thinks his favorite ice cream sandwiches are the trick to summoning his magic shield but learns otherwise when facing off with an acid-spewing insect monster.

added.title: Cheeseburger Backpack
added.description: A mission to the Lunar Sea Spire takes a treacherous turn, but Steven has packed his totally amazing Cheeseburger Backpack with anything they could ever need!

added.title: So Many Birthdays
added.description: So Many Birthdays: Steven learns that the Crystal Gems are thousands of years old and decides to make up for all the thousands of birthdays they've missed.

added.title: Be a Team
added.description: Mr. Gar brings in some team building experts to help KO, Enid and Rad.

added.title: Let's Watch the Boxmore Show
added.description: Our heroes discover that the Boxmore security camera feed is the most entertaining thing ever.

added.title: The So-Bad-Ical
added.description: When a new substitute shows up, KO and Dendy decide they need to get their old teacher back.

added.title: Wisdom, Strength, and Charisma
added.description: When Enid goes to a new school, KO sets out to make sure she fits in.

added.title: Are You Ready for Some Megafootball?!
added.description: Lakewood's Megafootball team takes on their rival in a big game.

added.title: Mystery Sleepover
added.description: KO, Enid and Rad attempt to solve a mystery.

added.title: Do You Have Any More in the Back?
added.description: Rad is put to the test when a customer needs something from the mysterious back room.

added.title: You Get Me
added.description: Enid gets turned to stone, and it's up to KO to turn her back to normal.

added.title: Glory Days
added.description: KO does a school report on Carol.

added.title: Mystery Science Fair 201X
added.description: KO helps Dendy with her science fair project.

added.title: Let's Not Be Skeletons
added.description: When a charismatic huckster shows up to the plaza, the product he's selling turns everything upside down.

added.title: Action News
added.description: Dynamite Watkins has to go extreme lengths breaking a new story.

added.title: Laundry Woes
added.description: Mordecai wants to return Margaret's sweater to her.

added.title: Every Meat Burritos
added.description: Mordecai, Rigby, Muscle Man and Fives want Every Meat Burritos from the Jimbros' Burritos drive-thru.

added.title: The Previous Owner
added.description: Each of the park guys want to win a bet by telling the scariest story at a Halloween party.

added.title: Power Tower
added.description: Muscle Man wants to win the bodybuilding competition at his gym.

added.title: Date with Gus
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa and Pizza Steve accidentally ruin Mr. Gus' night, the two of them go undercover as Mr. Gus's date.

added.title: Dodge This
added.description: The park guys want to win a dodge ball tournament.

added.title: In Your Footsteps
added.description: A bear befriends Finn and Jake, but what are his true intentions?

added.title: The Bike Ride
added.description: Pizza Steve desperately tries to prevent the gang from finding out his shameful secret.

added.title: Princess Cookie
added.description: Finn & Jake are called on to solve a Candy Kingdom hostage crisis when a rogue cookie takes over.

added.title: Birthday
added.description: Jeff and Sumo expect no one to show at Clarence's birthday party, just like last year. When dozens of kids arrive, the boys struggle to get face time with Clarence, the popular party host.

added.title: Uncle Easter
added.description: The Easter Bunny, unable to fulfill his egg-delivering duties, has Uncle Grandpa fill in for him.

added.title: Still
added.description: Finn and Jake find themselves paralyzed from the neck down and at the Ice King's mercy!

added.title: No One Can Hear You
added.description: Where are the citizens of Ooo?

added.title: Something He Ate
added.description: When Underbite eats part of the Autobots' GroundBridge, the Bee Team have to chase the teleporting 'Con through the desert, the forest, and even outer space!

added.title: Another Way
added.description: The tears of a crying Cyclops just might heal Finn and Jake's broken toes.

added.title: Five Fugitives
added.description: The Autobots' pursuit of Steeljaw hits an unexpected roadblock when Strongarm's old mentor DETECTIVE DROPFORGE arrives from Cybertron with orders to arrest the Bee Team!

added.title: Freedom Fighters
added.description: As the Bee Team struggles to liberate Cybertron from the Decepticon‑ controlled High Council, Optimus and his All Stars fight back the advance force of an Earth‑bound Cybertronian invasion!

added.title: Numbskull
added.description: A head Injury turns Mr. Gus into a bumbling fools whose wacky antics make him Uncle Grandpa's coolest friend. No longer the focus of Uncle Grandpa's attention, a jealous Pizza Steve tries to desperately to get back normal. Mr. Gus has to restore social balance in the RV.

added.title: Grudge Match
added.description: Ben and Kevin 11 are beamed up to a space ship where must learn to battle together in order to bring down a vicious alien fight promoter.

added.title: Spider Sense
added.description: When a monster ruins their relaxing vacation, the Girls run into a familiar face.

added.title: The Substitute
added.description: After Ms. Baker takes an unexpected personal day, she is replaced by a substitute that has a hard time handling the unruly classroom. Soon, the school day devolves into chaos and it is up to Clarence to get Mrs. Baker back to where she belongs, the classroom.

added.title: Find Your Bliss
added.description: When Bubbles blames a string of accidents on her imaginary friend "Bliss," her sisters begin to think she's lost her mind.

added.title: Plant Daddies
added.description: When Ms. Baker pairs up the kids to act as parents for a sprout, Sumo and Clarence learn all about good parenting. Jeff buys toys instead of fertilizer and Chelsea and Kimby get to know each other.

added.title: Tienes Mas Ahi Atras?
added.description: Rad se pone a prueba cuando un cliente necesita algo de la misteriosa habitación trasera.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Veamos el Show de Boxmore
added.description: Nuestros héroes descubren que las grabaciones de la cámara de seguridad de Boxmore son la cosa más divertida del mundo.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Trabajando en Equipo
added.description: El Sr. Gar trae a un equipo de expertos en construcción para que ayuden a K.O., Enid y Rad.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Mushroom Menace
added.description: The Mysterious Hooded Woman wants the Warriors For Hire to defend her giant pumpkin home from the dreaded Smashroom Mushroom, but Vambre and Prohyas can't complete their mission without help from Zombie Pumpkin Magisword!

added.title: Escape from Monster Island
added.description: After Bubbles wins two tickets to see the girls' favorite band Sensitive Thugz, Blossom and Buttercup vie for her plus one. But when the Mayor's plane crashes on Monster Island, the girls must put aside their differences to save the day!

added.title: And Then There Were 10
added.description: Ben discovers the Omnitrix, and when it attaches itself to Ben's wrist, he discovers it allows him to become any one of ten alien heroes.

added.title: Case Clothed
added.description: Princess Zange hires the Warriors to be her secret service for the afternoon to go shopping, but the looting pirates of Keelhaul Cove make fashion makeovers nearly impossible to manage.

added.title: Cleanliness Is Next to Grupliness
added.description: Grup has been stinking up the entire town of Rhyboflaven, but no matter how the Warriors try to lead the little dragon to water, they can't make him bathe!

added.title: Working for Scales
added.description: Princess Zange is sick and requires a dinosaur scale for a tea remedy, but King Rexxtopher is fiercely against the Warriors stepping foot inside his Dinosaur Kingdom to get it.

added.title: Potion in the Ocean
added.description: Witchy Simone joins the Warriors on a mission deep in the Fickle Sea to find an eye of newt for her magic potion, but Man Fish the Fish Man won't let them harm his sea newt pal!

added.title: Nature Clarence
added.description: Clarence, Sumo and Jeff's nature hike veers off course courtesy of their under qualified, overwhelmed guide Josh, prompting Clarence to take the lead.

added.title: Average Jeff
added.description: Jeff suffers an identity crisis when a standardized test lands him in the lesser of the classes academic groupings.

added.title: The Trouble with Truth
added.description: The JLA find themselves in danger of losing Wonder Woman when the goddess Athena comes to Earth with an offer Diana can't refuse, filling the position of the Goddess of Truth on Mt. Olympus.

added.title: All Aboard the Space Train
added.description: In a strange turn of events, the JLA enlist the help of Space Cabbie and Jonah Hex to stop the hijacking of an intergalactic space train.

added.title: Mxy's Mix-Up
added.description: As the Justice League is trying to protect the United Nations from Grodd's gorilla army, Mr. Mxyptlk pops up from the fifth dimension and thinks it would be great fun to put each of the superheroes' brains into another hero's body.

added.title: Booster's Gold
added.description: Green Arrow becomes involved with Booster Gold when he discovers that the self-centered superhero has brought dinosaurs back from the past for a money-making venture.

added.title: Secret Swapper of Doom
added.description: When the girls get a Paper Fortune Teller that can predict the future if they tell it a secret, they begin to rely on it to predict everything. But when it predicts the Powerpuff Girls will be destroyed, the girls must find a way to stop the future from happening.

added.title: Superman Red vs Superman Blue
added.description: Luthor comes up with the means to separate each Justice Leaguer in two, one passive and good, the other aggressive and mean.

added.title: Somewhere Over the Swingset
added.description: When the girls disobey the Professor and swing all the way over the swing set, they must deal with unexpected consequences.

added.title: Misfortune Cookie
added.description: After receiving an ominous fortune, Uncle Grandpa must snoop out whom among his friends is an enemy in disguise.

added.title: Blukic and Driba Go to Area 51
added.description: A mysterious Galvan arrives and demands Blukic and Driba to give back a super powerful weapon needed to stop a threat to Earth.

added.title: Universe vs. Tennyson
added.description: Ben gets dragged into intergalactic court by the other Celestialsapiens (Alien Xs) for recreating the universe (back in "So Long and Thanks for All the Smoothies").

added.title: The Secret of Dos Santos
added.description: Ben and Rook join Kai Green on a perilous alien relic hunt through South America.

added.title: Malgax Attacks
added.description: Ben finally manages to rid himself of Skurd... just when he needs the Slime-Biot most.

added.title: End of an Era
added.description: The Time War races towards its dramatic conclusion, with the fate of the entire universe and everything in it since the very beginning of time resting in the hands of the Ben 10.

added.title: Superfriends
added.description: The new girl next door learns it's hard to be best friends with superheroes and soon starts hanging out with the wrong kind of kid, Princess.

added.title: Telephonies/Tough Love
added.description: Telephonies: The Gangreen Gang gets hold of the Powerpuff Girls' Hotline and makes crank calls sending the Powerpuff Girls on a wild goose chases all over town./Tough Love: Everyone in Townsville loves the Powerpuff Girls! But the citizens have a sudden change of heart when Him sends out an evil gas turning the entire town against their favorite superheroes.

added.title: Roughing It Up/What's the Big Idea
added.description: Roughing It Up: The girls and the Professor set out on an old-fashioned vacation to the Townsville Swamp. Trouble is, Fuzzy and his nephews are there, too./What's the Big Idea: 20 story high Powerpuff Girls spell disaster for Townsville when they delicately try to stop Mojo from taking over.

added.title: Moral Decay/Meet the Beat Alls
added.description: Moral Decay: When Bubbles loses a tooth, she gets a shiny coin under her pillow the next day. Buttercup sees a gold mine in the mouths of Townsville's criminal element./Meet the Beat Alls: Mojo, Him, Princess and Fuzzy band together to form the Bad Four, a criminal supergroup out to destroy the Powerpuff Girls. Everything is going great until Mojo meets Moko Jono and falls in love.

added.title: The Exit/The Lost and the Cost
added.description: The Exit: The AO compete with a rival Brawling team for ViewTube hits leading to a "winner take all" brawl./The Lost and the Cost: Everett Ray, a promotor, tries to get the AO to join an official league for Bakugan Battling.

added.title: All Jungled Up/Outer Demons
added.description: All Jungled Up: Still lost in Vestroia the AO experience mind altering effects of the nearby Core Cell and come face to face with the Bakuzon monster Tiko./Outer Demons: The AO find the doorway out of Vestroia only to learn they have entered a mirror world of their own imagining created by the Core Cell.

added.title: Matter of the Mind/Core Cell
added.description: Matter of Mind: Drago leads the Bakugan against the threat of Tiko to protect a powerful energy source called the Core Cell./Core Cell: The AO defend the Core Cell from an attack by Tiko and in a last ditch effort to save it Dan manages to evolve Drago into his L2 form.

added.title: Subterranean Homesick Blues/Honey Struck
added.description: Subterranean Homesick Blues: The AO return home to learn that no time has passed but they soon discover their knowledge of brawling has gotten years more advanced./Honey Struck: After Strata is sent packing the AO discover that they have picked up a hitchhiker a Panda-like Bakugan who is nothing but sticky trouble.

added.title: Shun Shine/Ronin Son
added.description: Shun Shine: The AO want to evolve their Bakugan like Dan did with Drago but only Shun finds a way by tapping into the energy of the Mind Core Cell./Ronin Son: When Shun's cousin Masato Kazami claims Hydorous as his intellectual property the AO must battle to keep their friend by their side.

added.title: All Good in the Wood
added.description: When Suna and Ashley's science project turns into a hungry blob monster, Mega Man must team up with Wood Man to shut down the experiment gone wrong before it devours the city!

added.title: Fire Man in the Hole
added.description: While hiking on a dormant volcano, Aki sets out to retrieve Ashley's lost camera and, as Mega Man, to stop Fire Man from setting off an eruption!

added.title: A Split End
added.description: After replicating Cut Man's powers, Mega Man goes on a perfectionist spree, putting him on a collision course with Cut Man himself, whose latest stint as a hairdresser hasn't helped him overcome his own compulsions.

added.title: All Play and No Work
added.description: Mega Man must resist the influence of a prankster bot named Chaotique, whose devil may care ideology appeals to the overworked superhero, until his friends pay the price for his dalliances.

added.title: More More More!
added.description: In order to out-muscle Guts Man, Mega Man copies the big bot's schematics, and his insatiable appetite!

added.title: Blast Resort
added.description: Mega Man must assist Blasto Woman in a heist to stop a powerful EMP emitter from falling into the wrong hands.

added.title: Too Much Is Never Enough
added.description: Envious of Namagem's ability to wield more than three powers at a time, Mega Man tries taking all of his replicated schematics on board, with grave side effects.

added.title: The Bluster Bunch
added.description: A trail of tornadic destruction leads Mega Man, Suna, and Rush through a series of encounters with Air Man's quirky siblings.

added.title: Clarence and Sumo's Rexcellent Adventure
added.description: On a school trip to the Aberdale Natural History Museum, Clarence and Sumo check out the displays, goof around with the exhibits and even remove a tooth from the T-Rex display.

added.title: Merry Moochmas
added.description: It's wintertime in Aberdale and Clarence is convinced his winter wish for snow in Arizona will come true! However, his classmate Belson along with his grumpy cousin Gary Mooch are a little tougher to convince.

added.title: Sumo Goes West
added.description: Clarence learns his best friend Sumo may transfer to another school! It's up to Clarence to protest, petition and rally to convince everyone to let Sumo stay - or face losing his closest school pal!

added.title: Karate Mom
added.description: After surprising Clarence with Martial Arts classes at the "Aberdojo," Mary gets talked into joining the class herself. She loves the slow-paced lessons in discipline and control, but Clarence just wants to have fun and kick butt! Can Mary convince Clarence to stick with the class, earn his belt and have some fun with her?

added.title: Freedom Cactus
added.description: Clarence draws a comic for the school paper and it becomes a huge hit with the kids. When angry parents step in and censor the comic's crass humor, Clarence must stand up for his artistic vision.

added.title: Plane Excited
added.description: Clarence is all excited visit his grandma when he learns that Chad has never been on a plane. Clarence makes it his mission to help Chad get through a hectic flight.

added.title: Escape from Beyond the Cosmic
added.description: When Clarence accidentally breaks a local arcade game Jeff has become obsessed with, Clarence puts together his own real-life version of the game at home, encouraging Jeff to act out his fantasy in levels created exclusively by Clarence.

added.title: Money Broom Wizard
added.description: Can Clarence, Jeff and Sumo manage to have a good time at "Pizza Swamp" Arcade with only one dollar to spend between them? Yes.

added.title: Rise and Shine
added.description: A glimpse at the wild, secret adventures Clarence undertakes each day before the rest of us, and the sun, get up.

added.title: Slumber Party
added.description: Clarence struggles to make a connection at an all-girls slumber party, leaving Sumo and Jeff at odds without Clarence as their "friendship buffer."

added.title: Marceline Song Music Video
added.description: A song about Marceline written by Casey James Basichis.

added.title: Largo
added.description: When a mysterious rain cloud plagues Townsville, Bubbles learns things aren't what they seem.

added.title: The Long Skate Home
added.description: After they get accused of a crime they didn't commit, the Powerpuff girls and the Derbytantes have to find a way to clear their name!

added.title: In the Doghouse
added.description: Buttercup must go it alone to save her family from a kidnapping.

added.title: Derby Dollies
added.description: When Bubbles joins the Derbytantes, Buttercup finds herself on the sidelines.

added.title: Crazy Mixed Up Puffs/Mizzen in Action
added.description: Crazy Mixed Up Puffs: The girls must literally work as one to try and stop Mojo from destroying Townsville./Mizzen in Action: Captain Crack McGraigen and his crew are tossed forward in time where discover the chemical X that marks the spot and it is up to the girls and Professor to send the super-charged pirates back to their own time.

added.title: All Chalked Up
added.description: Him tricks Bubbles into bringing her chalk drawings to life, who then proceed to wreak havoc in Townsville.

added.title: Knock It Off
added.description: When the Professor's college roommate sees his old pal's brilliant creations, he decides to cash in on the popularity of the Powerpuffs.

added.title: Him Diddle Riddle
added.description: The Powerpuff Girls must solve a series of Him's riddles to keep the Professor from having to pay.

added.title: Candy Is Dandy/Catastrophe
added.description: Candy Is Dandy: When the Mayor gives the girls some candy in gratitude for saving the day, they become hooked on the stuff. They even make a deal with a local villain to commit crimes for treats./Catastrophe: A monster is frantically tearing up the town looking for his lost kitty. But in a city the size of Townsville, how can the girls find one lone cat?

added.title: Buttercrush/Fuzzy Logic
added.description: Buttercrush: Buttercup falls for Ace, the leader of the Gangreen Gang. But when the gang exploits her infatuation to lure Blossom and Bubbles into danger, Buttercup shows them the real meaning of the word crush./Fuzzy Logic: Beastly bumpkin Fuzzy Lumkins goes wild in Townsville and only the Powerpuff Girls, with some help from a flying squirrel, can teach him to respect other people's property.

added.title: Makes Zen to Me/Say Uncle
added.description: Makes Zen to Me: When Buttercup gets a fortune cookie saying peace lies within, the most violent of Powerpuffs sets out on a quest for inner peace./Say Uncle: The girls' go to pick up the Professor's brother at the train station, but mistake him for a wild-man being transported to the circus.

added.title: Silent Treatment/Sweet 'n' Sour
added.description: The Silent Treatment: When the girls go to see a silent movie with the Professor, they end up getting pulled into the film by an old-time villain./Sweet 'n' Sour: The girls must figure out how to beat Townsville's newest band of criminals: a group of adorable little animals.

added.title: The Status of Cattus
added.description: The Warriors want someone to enjoy collecting Magiswords as much as they do, so they go crazy trying to interest Cattus the Oneblade into obtaining more.

added.title: Team of Broccoli
added.description: The Warrior Family's broccoli crop is stolen and the Warriors and Danelda team up to track it down underground.

added.title: Agent of Destruction
added.description: DeBizz helps the Warriors become more famous as their agent, but Vambre returns to adventuring while Prohyas gets caught up in the DeBizz fame trap.

added.title: Dunkadellic
added.description: After suffering trauma from being the dunk-ee in a dunking booth, Prohyas has trouble getting through the dunk based traps in Man Fish's lair.

added.title: Broke His Crown
added.description: When Ice King's magic crown goes haywire, Marceline and Princess Bubblegum resort to extreme measures to help him.

added.title: Bun Bun
added.description: Finn brings a special delivery for Cinnamon Bun to the Fire Kingdom but it may come with a dangerous cost.

added.title: Daddy-Daughter Card Wars
added.description: To put his embarrassing past behind him, Jake needs his daughter Charlie's help to win an underground Card Wars tourney.

added.title: Jelly Beans Have Power
added.description: Princess Bubblegum's scientific mind must wrestle with her Elemental magic potential when she's faced with a Crystal Entity.

added.title: Wake Up
added.description: In order to find Finn's father, Finn and Jame must commit a cosmic crime...unless the Lich beats them to it.

added.title: Something Big
added.description: Princess Bubblegum must rally her forces when the Candy Kingdom is rocked by a massive assault.

added.title: Everything's Jake
added.description: Jake finds himself transported to a world both alien and familiar.
